    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> At the top of 3,500 meters an ice -cold wind was waiting for us - the 15 degrees felt like below zero. So quickly slipped into the sweat jacket and enjoyed the view. The air was thin, you felt that immediately. Basti decided not to go on - at least I wanted to try. But my knee, the steep steps and the height air then thwarted me. So back again. At least we were able to call a friend of the video by video call that Tenerife loves - that just had to be. </p>
        <p> Since there was not much more to discover up there, we drove down again after a short call with Bastis Mama. We actually wanted to eat something below, but everything was already closed - and that before 4 p.m. So Plan B: From to Vilaflor, the highest place on the island. The way there was ... sporty. It's a good thing that we didn't get the route up - our car would never have done that. </p>
        <p> In Vilaflor we found a restaurant directly, but there was nothing to eat there either. Just something to drink. After a short consideration we left the car and started - Google did not promise an Italian. And indeed: found - and finally something warm in the stomach. A little late, because soon there would be dinner in the hotel again ... but hunger was too big. </p>
        <p> Later we drove to Las America again. The search for the parking space was a little adventure, but at some point we were lucky. A little more sneaked through the shops, done a shopping order for our friends - and then we went back to the hotel. </p>
